latestPosts.caption:
Honestly I have changed how my skin looks with a few small habits ⬇️

> Your intake is everything 🍐🍏🍑
You literally reflect what you consume, so be mindful and choose food for your skin too.

> Drink your Vitamin C 🍊
More than applying vitamin C, drinking it has proven more benefits, you would anyway throw away the peel so better make tea out of it.

> Less is more 🤌
Several steps of skincare would not be of any good. Too much of product can actually clog your pores.
I usually use a toner, hydrating serum and a nourishing sunscreen as a part of my day skincare routine. Basically, I skip a moisturise as I am already hydrating it enough.

> Never skip sunscreen 🙅‍♀️
We already know this, we now have to make a habit of sticking to it.

Comment incase you need the recipe for the citrus tea 🫖

Always uploading reflection of the weekend to remind what is it all for ❤️
Also, so many of you asked for the grill fish recipe here it is:
Make a slurry of egg white, olive oil, lemon juice, chopped coriander & parsley, garlic paste, oregano, chilli flakes, pepper powder & salt, you may also add cornstarch to make everything hold better.
Now marinate the bhetki fillets in this slurry and keep if for rest for 10mints.
In a grill pan/fry pan (you can even use air fryer or oven), add little olive oil and fry the fish on both sides, in the pan add rosemary, lemon slice and generous amount of butter.
Serve with rice or salad of choice (I have used quinoa salad)
Happy eating ❤️

Ami Kolkata er Rosogolla 😌😍

Rosogolla is my first recipe I made as a creator. So, in 2020 there was a cooking competition in my previous organisation where we had to make something related to our culture, record a video and upload. 
Since we were in lockdown back then I thought of participating and the video came out decent or at least a lot better than I expected, my family suggested me to open a YouTube channel and upload it, so I did, the response was overwhelming so I continued posting one or two more YouTube videos and then stopped and ghosted away only until 2023 when I again started creating content on YouTube but totally neglected IG (I rather deactivated my IG for 6months in 2023) and then in 2024 I thought to try my luck here in Instagram and started consistently creating content and now just within a year, we are doing so good here 🫶
Oh btw, I also won in that cooking competition back in 2020 which means my Rosogolla video was actually a hit 😅
Ever since then I never made this recipe until this Jamai Shoshti and it was a hit again 🫶
Recipe:
Take full cream milk, bring it to boil , turn off the flame and add vinegar and water mix slowly until milk cuddles.
Now strain the water, wash the channa with clear water, squeeze out the water and keep it for straining placing a heavy item on top of it at least for 30mints so that all the excess water gets strain out.
Now take the channa and keep mixing it well with your palm for at least 15-20 mints or till the channa doesn’t stick to the plate anymore.
In a pan boil 1 cup of sugar with 4 cups of water and add some cardamom.
Give small round shape to the channa and drop them to the boiling water (note: don’t make the channa balls too big as it will double in size once it starts boiling)
Now cover and cook for 10 mints, again open and slip the Rosogolla on other side and cook for another 10mints.
Rest overnight or at least for 3-4hours and then enjoy.
Happy eating ❤️

Another year of Jamai Shoshti ❤️
This is our 5th year of Jamai Shoshti and only once my father could make it here, rest all the year we have been celebrating like this where I take up the responsibility to celebrate Ghosh barir jamai 🫶
This year, we had plans for my mom to show up and hence we didn’t plan a visit to Kolkata but last moment changes and we had to cancel my mom’s tickets.
We were so upset that we almost decided that we would just go out eat something, my mom on video call even whispered very softly the night before jamai shoshti “parle kichu banash nahole baire jamai ta k kichu bhalo khaye dish” (if you can then either cook something or make him eat something nice outside).
My heartfelt so heavy that I knew immediately, I can’t drop the ball and tried making some arrangements (even though whatever I do, however I do nothing can compensate the warmth of our parents), next year surely we will either be in Kolkata or they will be here 😊
Nonetheless, Ghosh barir er Jamai is satisfied ✨
In frame:
Rice, 5bhaja (begun, katla peti, uche, kumro, aloo), doi Potol, daal, goan prawn, bhetki grill, luchi aloo er dum, payesh, chutney, rossogolla, mishti doi, mango cheese ice cream & fruits.
Everything is home made apart from doi & ice cream ❤️

(Jamai shoshti, Bengali cuisine, Bengalis in Bangalore, food, lifestyle)
